The paper discusses probabilistic batch classifiers and their application in bio-informatics and image retrieval, indicating a focus on machine learning and data analysis. The use of indefinite similarity measures and the proposed algorithms for low rank indefinite kernels suggest a focus on linear algebra and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
